                <head>532. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>The results of the elections held in Thailand on December 15 were not decisive.
                    The final election returns were tabulated on December 27 and the vote was
                    broadly distributed among a wide range of political parties. The moderate
                    Unionist Party won 45 seats in Parliament and joined with the Army-supported
                    National Socialist Party to form a government under former Defense Minister
                    Thanom Kitti-kachorn.</p>
            </div>
